# Quick Start: Running Tests

## Step 1: Setup PostgreSQL

### Option A: Using Docker (Recommended)
```powershell
# Run PostgreSQL container
docker run --name postgres-utb-minute `
  -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres `
  -p 5432:5432 `
  -d postgres:latest

# Wait for PostgreSQL to start
Start-Sleep -Seconds 5
```

### Option B: Using Aspire AppHost
```powershell
cd "C:\Users\xs8x\Documents\AP_project\UTB.Minute"
dotnet run --project .\UTB.Minute.AppHost\
```

### Option C: Local PostgreSQL Installation
- Ensure PostgreSQL is running on `localhost:5432`
- Default user: `postgres`, password: `postgres`

## Step 2: Create Test Database

```powershell
# Using psql
psql -h localhost -U postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE utb_minute_test;"

# Or using Docker
docker exec postgres-utb-minute psql -U postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE utb_minute_test;"
```

## Step 3: Run Tests

### Quick Run (All Tests)
```powershell
cd "C:\Users\xs8x\Documents\AP_project\UTB.Minute"
dotnet test UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests
```

### Via Visual Studio
1. Open Solution Explorer
2. Navigate to `UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests` project
3. Open Test Explorer (Test → Test Explorer)
4. Click "Run All Tests"

### With Progress Information
```powershell
dotnet test UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests --logger "console;verbosity=detailed"
```

### Run Specific Test Category
```powershell
# Run only meal tests
dotnet test UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests --filter "ClassName=UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests.MealEndpointsTests"

# Run only menu item tests
dotnet test UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests --filter "ClassName=UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests.MenuItemEndpointsTests"

# Run only order tests
dotnet test UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests --filter "ClassName=UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests.OrderEndpointsTests"
```

### Run Single Test
```powershell
dotnet test UTB.Minute.WebApi.Tests --filter "Name=CreateMeal_WithValidData_ShouldReturnCreated"
```

