## Troubleshooting

### PostgreSQL Connection Failed
```powershell
# Check if PostgreSQL is running
docker ps | grep postgres

# Check connection manually
psql -h localhost -U postgres -d postgres

# View PostgreSQL logs (Docker)
docker logs postgres-utb-minute
```

### Test Database Already Exists
```powershell
# Drop and recreate (be careful!)
docker exec postgres-utb-minute psql -U postgres -c "DROP DATABASE utb_minute_test;"
docker exec postgres-utb-minute psql -U postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE utb_minute_test;"
```

### Tests Timeout or Hang
- Increase PowerShell timeout if needed
- Check PostgreSQL is responsive:
  ```powershell
  docker exec postgres-utb-minute psql -U postgres -c "SELECT version();"
  ```

